      "id": "PopularPost308547",
      "post_content": "This card was practically unplayable when it released, since Magic was still using the batch rules (which sucked and didn't actually work.) Then, when Sixth Edition introduced the stack, Death Spark became one of the best recurring burn spells ever, arguably better than Hammer of Bogardan due to instant speed and 133% as much damage per mana spent (8 for 3 vs. 2 for 1.)  \n  \nThen damage got removed from the stack and Death Spark took a hit, but it's still pretty awesome. Plus dat art.",
